// Carrier autopilot for EMM-A system.
// Broadcasts dock connector pose and supports nav/path autopilot.
//
// ============= Commands ==============
// Nav;GPS:Name:X:Y:Z:|Ux,Uy,Uz,Fx,Fy,Fz : set target position and orientation vectors
// Nav;GPS:Name:X:Y:Z:|Faceup,Faceforward  : auto-derive up/forward toward target
// pause        : pause updates and release controls without clearing current task
// resume/start : resume after pause
// stop         : abort current task, clear target, and release controls
// reset        : clear target and all path state
// dumpgps      : save current GPS + orientation to Custom Data
// pathstart    : load records from "Carrier Path" timer and execute row-by-row
// pathpause    : pause path execution
// pathcontinue : resume path after pause
// pathstop     : stop path mode and clear queued records
// TOFF r,u,f   : set target offset in local Right,Up,Forward meters
// TOFFRESET    : reset target offset to 0,0,0
// saveasteroid : simulate recompile, then save carrier pos, miner ore totals, and miner
//                path into the next Asteroid Record slot across "EMM-A Ca Asteroid DB Axx"
//                timers (asteroidsPerDb records each). Also updates the active zone's Zone DB
//                selected from "EMM-A Ca Zone DB Registry". Clears the miner's path timer.
// Missing ore names are auto-added to timer "EMM-A Ca Ores" custom data
// in format: <OreName> on
// <OreName> on/off : set one ore row state in "EMM-A Ca Ores" (example: Iron off)
// Fullauto     : auto-select nearest Open asteroid with enabled ore(s) and run Mine loop
// Fullautostop : stop Fullauto loop (does not forcibly cancel an in-progress Mine step)
// setallopen   : set all asteroid status lines in the active zone's Zone DB to "Open" (adds missing lines).
// dbcheck      : cross-validate all registered Zone DBs vs Asteroid DB timers; lists orphaned entries in each.
// dbcheck;fix  : same as dbcheck, then removes Zone DB entries with no Asteroid DB path data.
// audit        : append duplicate Zone ID report to Custom Data.
// LoadAsteroid <n> : load the path records from the saved Asteroid record <n> (e.g. 002)
//                    into the miner's "EMM-A Mi Path" timer, replacing its current content.
//
// Persistent on-disk format (path timer / Asteroid DB / Zone DB):
//   carrier anchor : cx,cy,cz:ax,ay,az,a     -- absolute pos + axis-angle rotation
//   path point     : dx,dy,dz:ax,ay,az,a     -- delta from anchor + axis-angle
//   mine area      : dx,dy,dz:ax,ay,az,a:w,h:depth -- corner-A delta, area axis-angle, w/h, depth
// Player-pasted "GPS:Name:X:Y:Z:|..." waypoints are still accepted by the Nav;... command
// and as path-timer entries.
// GoTo <n>         : approach saved Asteroid <n> from a safe side-point, then fly/align to saved
//                    carrier pose while avoiding the asteroid bubble around the saved site.
// Mine <n>         : orchestrates GoTo <n> -> LoadAsteroid <n> -> miner PathStart -> wait for miner
//                    path completion broadcast -> move to front approach point and finish.
// =====================================

